receivedRecommendations.description: No one matches Zack in terms of pure horsepower.  In the amount of time most Booth students would spend on a single class, Zack would not only exhaust the assigned course material, but also supplement his knowledge by seeking out additional textbooks and articles.  Through a combination of unshakeable focus, infallible efficiency, and self-competitive dedication, Zack advanced his knowledge at a pace that was unmatched.  The results are evident; in addition to a demanding engineering job and his MBA coursework, Zack cleared two CFA levels and navigated a career switch to a top-tier investment bank - all at the same time, and to the bewilderment of his classmates. receivedRecommendations.givenAt: March 9, 2011, Jon and Zachary studied together
receivedRecommendations.description:
I have had the pleasure of knowing Zack Rigoni since 2007 and had the privilege of working closely with him for two of those years as colleagues at the University of Chicago Booth School of Business.  While Zack’s qualifications certainly speak for themselves, there are some important things that can’t be conveyed as acutely by his résumé; his tenacity, passion, and dedication.
 
Zack was consistently the first to show up to school and the last one to leave.  And it wasn’t because he was a slow worker—it was because he took on more than any other student I knew.  He took many of the hardest courses offered at Chicago Booth taught by notoriously difficult professors, while balancing that at various points with being the chair of the Banking and Energy Clubs, studying for the CFA exam, and playing in a band on the weekends.  To graduate with honors in addition to all this was nothing short of astonishing.  In addition, he left a promising career with high trajectory at an engineering firm because he found that his passion was in finance.  And he pursued this path as fervently as he has pursued all his other passions, obtaining various internships and positions to prove to the world that he could not only handle the finance world, but thrive in it and, ultimately, help shape it.
 
Dedication without the skills to back it up can be unproductive, but this has never been a problem for Zack because both his technical and inter-personal skills are all well-suited to help him meet his lofty goals.  He’s one of the few people I know for whom I can confidently say that any challenge I have seen him approach, I have also seen him conquer.  This is a staunch testament to the qualities that he has worked so hard to imbue in himself.
